    summary: '为回应埃德萨伯国陷落，法王路易七世与德王康拉德三世率军东征，但在大马士革遭遇惨败，标志着十字军国家开始衰落。',
    summaryEn: 'Responding to the fall of Edessa, King Louis VII of France and King Conrad III of Germany led an expedition that ended in disaster at Damascus, signaling the decline of the Crusader states.',
    description: '1144年，穆斯林领袖赞吉攻占埃德萨伯国（第一个建立的十字军国家），震动西欧。教皇尤金三世号召第二次十字军东征，由克莱尔沃的伯纳德布道激发。法王路易七世和德意志国王康拉德三世分别率大军东征。康拉德的德军在穿越安纳托利亚时遭到塞尔柱突厥人的伏击，损失惨重；路易的法国军队也历经艰险。1148年，残余十字军与耶路撒冷王国联军决定攻打穆斯林控制的大马士革，但在围城仅四天后即被迫撤退。此次失败标志着十字军不可战胜的神话破灭，伊斯兰世界开始转入反攻，十字军国家逐渐失去战略主动权。',
    descriptionEn: 'In 1144, the Muslim leader Zengi captured the County of Edessa, the first Crusader state to be established, shocking Western Europe. Pope Eugene III called for the Second Crusade, preached by Bernard of Clairvaux. King Louis VII of France and King Conrad III of Germany each led large armies eastward. Conrad\'s German force was ambushed by Seljuk Turks crossing Anatolia and suffered severe losses; Louis\'s French army also endured great hardship. In 1148, the remaining crusader forces joined with the Kingdom of Jerusalem to attack Damascus but were forced to retreat after only four days of siege. The disaster shattered the myth of crusader invincibility and marked the beginning of the Islamic counter-offensive against the Crusader states.',
