    summary: '塔里克·伊本·齐亚德率柏柏尔-阿拉伯联军跨海征服西哥特王国，开启近800年的穆斯林西班牙（安达卢斯）时代。',
    summaryEn: 'Tariq ibn Ziyad led a Berber-Arab force across the Strait of Gibraltar, conquering the Visigothic Kingdom and inaugurating nearly eight centuries of Muslim Spain (al-Andalus).',
    description: '711年，伍麦叶王朝将领塔里克·伊本·齐亚德率约7000名柏柏尔战士从北非跨过直布罗陀海峡（海峡名称即源于其名，贾巴尔·塔里克意为"塔里克之山"）登陆伊比利亚半岛。同年7月，他在瓜达莱特战役中击败并杀死西哥特国王罗德里克。此后数年内，穆斯林军队以惊人速度征服了半岛大部分地区，西哥特王国迅速崩溃。穆斯林统治的西班牙被称为"安达卢斯"，科尔多瓦、格拉纳达、塞维利亚等发展成为欧洲最繁盛的文明城市，在科学、哲学和文化上领先于基督教欧洲数百年。基督教势力在北部山区组织抵抗，缓慢的"收复失地运动"（Reconquista）耗时近八百年。',
    descriptionEn: 'In 711 CE, Umayyad general Tariq ibn Ziyad led about 7,000 Berber warriors across the Strait of Gibraltar (whose name derives from Jabal Tariq, "Mountain of Tariq") to land on the Iberian Peninsula. In July of that year, he defeated and killed the Visigothic king Roderic at the Battle of Guadalete. Within a few years, Muslim forces conquered most of the peninsula with astonishing speed as the Visigothic kingdom collapsed. Muslim-ruled Spain, known as al-Andalus, saw Córdoba, Granada, and Seville become the most prosperous cities in Europe, leading Christian Europe in science, philosophy, and culture for centuries. Christian powers in the northern mountains organized a slow resistance—the Reconquista—that would take nearly eight centuries to complete.',
