    summary: '查理曼的三个孙子将加洛林帝国一分为三，奠定了现代法国、德国和意大利的地缘政治基础。',
    summaryEn: 'Charlemagne\'s three grandsons divided the Carolingian Empire into three parts, laying the geopolitical foundations of modern France, Germany, and Italy.',
    description: '843年，查理曼大帝的三个孙子——洛泰尔一世、日耳曼人路易和秃头查理——在凡尔登签订条约，将庞大的加洛林帝国正式划分为三个独立王国。洛泰尔获得中法兰克王国（从北海延伸至意大利的狭长地带，含皇帝头衔），日耳曼人路易获得东法兰克王国（大致相当于现代德国），秃头查理获得西法兰克王国（大致相当于现代法国）。这一分裂永久性地塑造了欧洲政治版图。中法兰克王国很快再次分裂，其北部（洛林/阿尔萨斯）在此后千年中成为法德争夺的焦点。凡尔登条约被许多历史学家视为现代欧洲民族国家体系的地理和政治起点。',
    descriptionEn: 'In 843 CE, the three grandsons of Charlemagne—Lothair I, Louis the German, and Charles the Bald—signed the Treaty of Verdun, formally dividing the vast Carolingian Empire into three independent kingdoms. Lothair received Middle Francia (a strip from the North Sea to Italy, retaining the imperial title), Louis the German received East Francia (roughly modern Germany), and Charles the Bald received West Francia (roughly modern France). This division permanently shaped the political map of Europe. Middle Francia soon fragmented further, and its northern part (Lorraine/Alsace) became the contested ground between France and Germany for the next millennium. Many historians regard the Treaty of Verdun as the geographic and political starting point of the modern European nation-state system.',
