    description: '约982年，红发埃里克因在冰岛犯下杀人罪被放逐三年，他航行至西方发现了一片覆盖冰川和草地的巨大岛屿。为吸引移民，他将其命名为"格陵兰"（绿色的土地）。985年，他率领25艘船、约500名移民从冰岛出发，仅14艘抵达格陵兰南部峡湾，建立了东定居点和西定居点。这些北欧殖民地繁荣了数百年，人口最多时约3000-5000人，基督教在11世纪传入。约1000年，埃里克的儿子莱夫·埃里克松从格陵兰出发，成为第一个踏上北美大陆的欧洲人。格陵兰北欧殖民地在15世纪神秘消失，可能因气候变化和小冰河期的来临。',
    descriptionEn: 'Around 982 CE, Erik the Red, banished from Iceland for manslaughter, sailed westward and discovered a vast island of glaciers and grasslands. To attract settlers, he named it "Greenland." In 985, he led 25 ships with about 500 settlers from Iceland, of which only 14 reached the southern fjords, establishing the Eastern and Western Settlements. These Norse colonies flourished for centuries with a peak population of 3,000-5,000, and Christianity arrived in the 11th century. Around the year 1000, Erik\'s son Leif Eriksson sailed from Greenland to become the first European to set foot on continental North America (Vinland). The Greenland Norse colonies mysteriously vanished in the 15th century, possibly due to climate change and the onset of the Little Ice Age.',
