    summary: '源赖朝被朝廷正式任命为征夷大将军，在镰仓开设幕府，开启日本近700年的武士政权时代。',
    summaryEn: 'Minamoto no Yoritomo was formally appointed Seii Taishogun by the imperial court and established his bakufu in Kamakura, inaugurating nearly 700 years of samurai rule in Japan.',
    description: '在源平合战（1180-1185）中击败平氏后，源赖朝在关东地区建立了以武士为基础的新政治体制。1192年，朝廷正式任命源赖朝为"征夷大将军"，他于镰仓建立了日本历史上第一个武家政权——镰仓幕府。通过设立守护和地头制度，幕府将全国置于有效的军事管辖之下。虽然京都的天皇朝廷形式上仍然存在，但实权已转移到镰仓的将军和武士手中。镰仓幕府的建立标志着日本从平安时代的贵族统治转变为武士统治的封建社会，这一格局持续到明治维新（1868年）。镰仓时期还经历了蒙古入侵（1274年、1281年）这一日本历史上最大的外部威胁。',
    descriptionEn: 'After defeating the Taira clan in the Genpei War (1180-1185), Minamoto no Yoritomo built a new warrior-based political system in the Kanto region. In 1192, the imperial court formally appointed him Seii Taishogun ("Barbarian-Subduing Great General"), and he established Japan\'s first warrior government—the Kamakura Shogunate. Through the offices of shugo (military governors) and jito (land stewards), the shogunate placed the country under effective military administration. Although the imperial court in Kyoto nominally persisted, real power shifted to the shogun and warriors in Kamakura. The founding of the shogunate marks Japan\'s transformation from Heian-era aristocratic rule to feudal samurai governance, a system that endured until the Meiji Restoration of 1868. The Kamakura period also witnessed the Mongol invasions (1274, 1281), Japan\'s greatest external threat before the modern era.',
