    summaryEn: 'Isabella and Ferdinand obtained papal authorization to establish the Spanish Inquisition, primarily targeting Jewish converts and Muslims, leaving a profound mark on Spanish history.',
    description: '1478年，天主教君主伊莎贝拉一世和斐迪南二世获得教皇西克斯图斯四世的批准，在卡斯蒂利亚建立了西班牙宗教裁判所。与中世纪的教廷宗教裁判所不同，西班牙裁判所直接受国王控制，是国家与教会权力的结合。其主要目标是调查"改宗者"（conversos，被迫改信基督教的犹太人和穆斯林）是否秘密保留了原信仰。在首任大裁判官托马斯·德·托尔克马达的铁腕领导下，裁判所使用酷刑逼供和火刑处决，据估计约2000-3000人在其活跃时期被处死。1492年，君主同时完成了格拉纳达征服、驱逐犹太人、资助哥伦布远航三件大事，宗教裁判所正是这一系列举措的组成部分。',
    descriptionEn: 'In 1478, the Catholic Monarchs Isabella I of Castile and Ferdinand II of Aragon obtained papal authorization from Sixtus IV to establish the Spanish Inquisition in Castile. Unlike the medieval Papal Inquisition, the Spanish Inquisition was directly under royal control, a fusion of state and church power. Its primary target was "conversos" (Jews and Muslims forced to convert to Christianity) suspected of secretly practicing their original faiths. Under the first Grand Inquisitor Tomás de Torquemada, the Inquisition used torture and burning at the stake; an estimated 2,000-3,000 people were executed. The year 1492 saw the Catholic Monarchs complete three monumental acts: the conquest of Granada, the expulsion of the Jews, and the sponsorship of Columbus\'s voyage—the Inquisition was integral to this program.',
