    summary: '天主教会的全体大公会议，在应对新教改革的背景下重新确立教会教义、整顿纪律，开启了天主教反宗教改革运动。',
    summaryEn: 'An ecumenical council of the Catholic Church that redefined doctrine and reformed discipline in response to the Protestant Reformation, launching the Catholic Counter-Reformation.',
    description: '1545年至1563年间，天主教会在意大利北部城市特伦托（Trento）召开了其历史上最重要的大公会议之一。在教皇保罗三世发起下，大会分三个阶段断断续续地召开。会议重新确认了天主教的核心教义——包括圣经与圣传同为权威来源、七项圣事、变体论和炼狱的存在——明确否定了新教的核心主张。同时，会议进行了重大内部改革：禁止圣职买卖、要求主教驻在教区、建立神学院培养神职人员、规范婚姻法律。特伦多大公会议标志着天主教反宗教改革的正式启动，其决议塑造了此后400年的天主教面貌，直到20世纪的第二次梵蒂冈大公会议才做出重大修正。',
    descriptionEn: 'Between 1545 and 1563, the Catholic Church convened one of its most important ecumenical councils in the northern Italian city of Trento. Summoned by Pope Paul III, the council met in three interrupted sessions. It reaffirmed core Catholic doctrines—including Scripture and Tradition as twin authorities, the seven sacraments, transubstantiation, and the existence of Purgatory—explicitly rejecting Protestant claims. Simultaneously, it enacted major internal reforms: banning simony, requiring bishops to reside in their dioceses, establishing seminaries for priestly formation, and regularizing marriage law. The Council of Trent formally launched the Catholic Counter-Reformation, and its decisions shaped Catholic identity for the next four centuries until the Second Vatican Council (1962-1965) introduced substantial modifications.',
