    summaryEn: 'Parliament invited the Dutch Stadtholder William III to England, overthrew James II in a bloodless coup, and established constitutional monarchy through the Bill of Rights.',
    description: '1688年，英格兰国王詹姆斯二世的天主教倾向和专制统治引发了政治精英的普遍不满。七位显贵（"不朽七人"）秘密邀请詹姆斯的新教徒女儿玛丽及其丈夫荷兰执政威廉三世率军入英。威廉于11月登陆，詹姆斯二世仓皇出逃法国。1689年初，协商议会召集威廉和玛丽共同登基，同时通过了《权利法案》，明确规定未经议会同意国王不得废止法律、征税或维持常备军。光荣革命被视为不流血的革命，确立了议会主权原则和君主立宪制度，为英国此后三百年的政治稳定奠定了基础，也成为启蒙运动思想家（如洛克）阐述社会契约论的现实灵感来源。',
    descriptionEn: 'By 1688, King James II\'s Catholicism and absolutist tendencies had alienated the English political elite. Seven notables (the "Immortal Seven") secretly invited James\'s Protestant daughter Mary and her husband William III of Orange to intervene. William landed in November and James fled to France. In early 1689, the Convention Parliament offered the crown jointly to William and Mary, while passing the Bill of Rights, which explicitly prohibited the monarch from suspending laws, levying taxes, or maintaining a standing army without parliamentary consent. The Glorious Revolution is celebrated as a bloodless revolution that established parliamentary sovereignty and constitutional monarchy, laying the foundation for Britain\'s political stability over the next three centuries. It also provided the real-world inspiration for Enlightenment thinkers like John Locke to articulate social contract theory.',
