    summary: '彼得大帝在北方大战期间于涅瓦河沼泽地上建立新都圣彼得堡，使之成为俄罗斯通往欧洲的"窗口"。',
    summaryEn: 'Peter the Great founded his new capital St. Petersburg on the swamps of the Neva River during the Great Northern War, creating Russia\'s "window to Europe."',
    description: '1703年5月27日，在北方大战（1700-1721）中俄军刚刚夺取涅瓦河口地区后，彼得大帝亲手铲下了圣彼得堡的第一块基石。在沼泽遍布、气候恶劣的涅瓦河三角洲上，彼得以近乎残酷的手段调集数万农奴，在短短十年内建起了一座拥有宏伟宫殿、宽广街道和海军基地的欧式都城。他聘请意大利、法国和荷兰建筑师设计，以当时欧洲最先进的巴洛克风格建造。1712年，彼得正式将首都从莫斯科迁至圣彼得堡，使之成为俄罗斯的政治、文化和海军中心。这座城市体现了彼得的西化改革理念——打破俄罗斯的孤立传统，使其融入欧洲现代化进程。圣彼得堡在随后两百年间一直是俄罗斯帝国的首都。',
    descriptionEn: 'On May 27, 1703, during the Great Northern War (1700-1721), shortly after Russian forces had seized the mouth of the Neva River, Peter the Great personally laid the foundation stone of St. Petersburg. On the swampy, inhospitable Neva delta, Peter deployed tens of thousands of serfs under brutal conditions to build a European-style capital with grand palaces, wide boulevards, and a naval base within a decade. He hired Italian, French, and Dutch architects, building in the most advanced Baroque style of the era. In 1712, Peter formally transferred the capital from Moscow to St. Petersburg, making it Russia\'s political, cultural, and naval center. The city embodied Peter\'s Westernizing vision—breaking Russia\'s isolation and integrating it into the European modernizing process. St. Petersburg remained the capital of the Russian Empire for the next two centuries.',
