    importance: 5,
    summary: '罗伯斯庇尔领导的公安委员会以革命的名义处决数万人，"革命的恐怖"成为法国大革命最血腥和最具争议的阶段。',
    summaryEn: 'Robespierre\'s Committee of Public Safety executed tens of thousands in the name of revolution, making the Terror the bloodiest and most controversial phase of the French Revolution.',
    description: '1793年9月至1794年7月，面对内外交困的危机——外国联军入侵、旺代保王党叛乱和经济崩溃——罗伯斯庇尔领导的公安委员会以"革命的恐怖"为手段巩固政权。1793年9月颁布的《嫌疑人法》授权大规模逮捕"自由的敌人"。革命法庭在巴黎审判并处决了约2,600人（包括王后玛丽·安托瓦内特、吉伦特派领袖和丹东），通过断头台的行刑成为日常景观。外省的镇压更为残酷，旺代地区的平叛造成数十万人死亡。1794年7月27日（热月9日），国民公会中的反对派联合推翻并逮捕了罗伯斯庇尔及其追随者，次日将他们送上断头台，恐怖统治骤然终结。热月政变标志着法国大革命激进阶段的结束。',
    descriptionEn: 'From September 1793 to July 1794, facing existential crises—foreign invasion, the Royalist Vendée rebellion, and economic collapse—Robespierre\'s Committee of Public Safety consolidated power through "Revolutionary Terror." The Law of Suspects (September 1793) authorized mass arrests of "enemies of liberty." The Revolutionary Tribunal in Paris tried and executed about 2,600 people, including Queen Marie Antoinette, Girondin leaders, and Danton, as guillotine executions became daily spectacle. Repression in the provinces was even more brutal, with the Vendée pacification causing hundreds of thousands of deaths. On July 27, 1794 (9 Thermidor), a coalition in the Convention overthrew and arrested Robespierre and his followers, sending them to the guillotine the next day. The Terror ended abruptly. The Thermidorian Reaction marked the close of the radical phase of the French Revolution.',
