    summaryEn: 'A massive uprising of Indian soldiers and civilians against British rule. Though suppressed, it ended East India Company rule and brought India under direct Crown governance.',
    description: '1857年5月，驻扎在密拉特的印度籍士兵（Sepoy）因拒绝使用据说涂有猪油和牛脂的子弹（冒犯了穆斯林和印度教徒的宗教禁忌）发动兵变，迅速演变为席卷印度北部和中部的反英大起义。起义军在德里拥立了年迈的莫卧儿皇帝巴哈杜尔·沙二世为名义领袖，出现了占西女王拉克希米·芭伊等传奇女性将领。英国经过数月血腥战斗，于1857年9月重新控制德里。起义于1858年基本被镇压，双方均有大量暴行。起义的直接后果是英国议会通过《1858年印度政府法》，解散东印度公司，印度由英国王室直接统治。1877年，维多利亚女王加冕为印度女皇。这场起义被印度民族主义者视为第一次独立战争的精神先驱。',
    descriptionEn: 'In May 1857, Indian soldiers (Sepoys) stationed at Meerut mutinied over cartridges reportedly greased with cow and pig fat, offending both Hindu and Muslim religious taboos. The mutiny rapidly escalated into a widespread anti-British uprising across northern and central India. The rebels proclaimed the aged Mughal emperor Bahadur Shah II as their nominal leader in Delhi, and produced legendary figures like the Rani of Jhansi, Lakshmibai. The British recaptured Delhi in September 1857 after months of bloody fighting, and the rebellion was largely suppressed by 1858, with atrocities committed by both sides. The immediate consequence was the Government of India Act 1858, dissolving the East India Company and transferring governance directly to the British Crown. In 1877, Queen Victoria was proclaimed Empress of India. Indian nationalists later revered the rebellion as the spiritual precursor to the independence movement.',
