    description: '1899年至1901年，以义和拳（又称义和团）为中心的华北民间反帝运动达到高潮。义和团宣扬刀枪不入的拳术和符咒，以"扶清灭洋"为口号，焚烧教堂、杀害传教士和华人基督徒、破坏铁路和电报线。1900年6月，慈禧太后在犹豫后支持义和团向十一国宣战，义和团和清军围攻北京东交民巷的外国使馆区55天。同年8月，英、美、法、德、俄、日、意、奥八国联军攻入北京，慈禧和光绪帝西逃西安。1901年9月7日签订的《辛丑条约》要求中国支付4.5亿两白银（本息合计9.8亿两）的巨额赔款，并允许外国在使馆区和山海关沿线驻军，中国主权进一步沦丧。',
    descriptionEn: 'From 1899 to 1901, the anti-foreign movement centered on the "Boxers United in Righteousness" (Yihequan) reached its peak in northern China. The Boxers, claiming invulnerability through martial arts and magical charms and chanting "Support the Qing, destroy the foreigners," burned churches, killed missionaries and Chinese Christians, and destroyed railways and telegraph lines. In June 1900, the Empress Dowager Cixi, after initial hesitation, threw her support behind the Boxers and declared war on eleven foreign powers. Boxers and Qing troops besieged the foreign legation quarter in Beijing for 55 days. In August, an Eight-Nation Alliance force (Britain, US, France, Germany, Russia, Japan, Italy, Austria-Hungary) captured Beijing; Cixi and the Guangxu Emperor fled to Xi\'an. The Boxer Protocol of September 7, 1901, demanded 450 million taels of silver in reparations—the largest indemnity in Chinese history—and permitted foreign garrisons along the route to the capital, further eroding Chinese sovereignty.',
