    summary: '日本在近代首次击败欧洲列强，旅顺和对马海战的胜利震动了全球，标志着亚洲力量在世界舞台上的崛起。',
    summaryEn: 'Japan\'s first modern defeat of a European great power, with victories at Port Arthur and Tsushima stunning the world and signaling Asia\'s rise on the global stage.',
    description: '1904-1905年，日本和俄罗斯为争夺中国东北和朝鲜半岛的控制权爆发战争。1904年2月，日本海军未经宣战突袭旅顺港的俄国太平洋舰队。在陆上，日军以惨重代价攻下旅顺要塞（203高地），并在奉天战役中击败俄军主力。战争的决定性时刻是1905年5月27-28日的对马海战：东乡平八郎指挥的日本联合舰队全歼了从波罗的海远航18000海里而来的俄国第二太平洋舰队。由美国总统西奥多·罗斯福调停的《朴茨茅斯和约》使日本获得朝鲜的控制权和在满洲南部的特权。这是近代史上亚洲国家首次击败欧洲列强，极大地鼓舞了亚洲各地的民族主义运动，同时暴露了沙皇俄国的腐朽，直接催化了1905年俄国革命。',
    descriptionEn: 'The Russo-Japanese War (1904-1905) was fought over control of Manchuria and the Korean Peninsula. In February 1904, the Japanese navy launched a surprise torpedo attack on the Russian Pacific Fleet at Port Arthur. On land, Japanese forces captured Port Arthur\'s fortress (Hill 203) at great cost and defeated Russian forces at the Battle of Mukden. The war\'s decisive moment came at the Battle of Tsushima on May 27-28, 1905: Admiral Togo Heihachiro\'s Combined Fleet annihilated the Russian Baltic Fleet, which had sailed 18,000 nautical miles from Europe. The Treaty of Portsmouth, mediated by US President Theodore Roosevelt, gave Japan control over Korea and privileges in southern Manchuria. This was the first modern defeat of a European power by an Asian nation, electrifying nationalist movements across Asia, while exposing tsarist Russia\'s decay and directly catalyzing the 1905 Russian Revolution.',
