    summaryEn: 'A nationwide revolutionary wave triggered by defeat in the Russo-Japanese War, forcing Nicholas II to issue the October Manifesto promising a Duma and civil liberties—a prelude to 1917.',
    description: '1905年1月22日（俄历1月9日），即"血腥星期日"，数以万计的工人在神父加邦的带领下和平游行至冬宫前请愿，军队开火造成数百人死伤，瞬间点燃全国革命。工人罢工、农民暴动、少数民族起义和军队中的兵变（波将金号战舰事件）席卷帝国。10月，全国总罢工使俄国陷入瘫痪。在巨大压力下，沙皇尼古拉二世于10月30日颁布《十月宣言》，承诺保障公民自由、扩大选举权并建立国家杜马（议会）。尽管革命被逐步镇压，杜马实权有限，但这是俄国历史上第一次大规模的人民反抗运动，为12年后的1917年革命提供了宝贵经验。列宁称1905年为1917年的"总演习"。',
    descriptionEn: 'On January 22, 1905 (January 9, Old Style)—"Bloody Sunday"—tens of thousands of workers led by Father Gapon marched peacefully to the Winter Palace with a petition. Troops opened fire, killing and wounding hundreds, instantly igniting revolution nationwide. Workers\' strikes, peasant uprisings, minority national rebellions, and military mutinies (the Battleship Potemkin incident) swept the empire. By October, a general strike paralyzed Russia. Under immense pressure, Tsar Nicholas II issued the October Manifesto on October 30, promising civil liberties, expanded suffrage, and a State Duma (parliament). Though the revolution was gradually suppressed and the Duma\'s real power was limited, 1905 was Russia\'s first mass popular movement against autocracy and provided invaluable experience for the 1917 Revolution twelve years later. Lenin called 1905 the "dress rehearsal" for 1917.',
