    summary: '人类首次在战争中使用原子弹，美国B-29轰炸机在广岛投下"小男孩"原子弹，瞬间摧毁整个城市，深刻改变了战争与世界格局。',
    summaryEn: 'The first use of an atomic weapon in warfare: the US B-29 bomber Enola Gay dropped "Little Boy" on Hiroshima, obliterating the city and fundamentally transforming warfare and global geopolitics.',
    description: '1945年8月6日上午8时15分，美国陆军航空队的B-29"埃诺拉·盖伊"号轰炸机在广岛市中心投下了一枚名为"小男孩"的铀弹原子弹。炸弹在约600米高空爆炸，瞬间产生数千度的高温火球和巨大冲击波，半径两公里内的建筑几乎全部被夷为平地。当天估计约7万-8万人当场死亡，到1945年底死亡人数上升至约14万人。三天后（8月9日），第二枚原子弹"胖子"被投在长崎。8月15日，日本天皇裕仁宣布无条件投降，第二次世界大战正式结束。广岛和长崎的原子弹爆炸标志着核时代的开启，此后的冷战格局与国际安全秩序都建立在核威慑的恐怖平衡之上。',
    descriptionEn: 'At 8:15 AM on August 6, 1945, the US Army Air Forces B-29 bomber "Enola Gay" dropped the uranium-fueled atomic bomb "Little Boy" over the center of Hiroshima. The bomb detonated at approximately 600 meters altitude, generating a fireball of several thousand degrees and a massive blast wave that leveled nearly all buildings within a two-kilometer radius. An estimated 70,000-80,000 people died instantly that day, rising to approximately 140,000 by the end of 1945. Three days later (August 9), a second atomic bomb, "Fat Man," was dropped on Nagasaki. On August 15, Emperor Hirohito announced Japan\'s unconditional surrender, formally ending World War II. The Hiroshima and Nagasaki bombings inaugurated the nuclear age, and the subsequent Cold War and international security order were built upon the terrifying balance of nuclear deterrence.',
