    summary: '冷战时期第一场大规模热战，以美国为首的联合国军与中国志愿军在三八线附近反复拉锯，最终以停战协定而非和平条约告终。',
    summaryEn: 'The first large-scale hot war of the Cold War, with UN forces under US command and Chinese volunteers fighting to a stalemate near the 38th parallel, ending in an armistice rather than a peace treaty.',
    description: '1950年6月25日，朝鲜人民军越过三八线南下，迅速占领了半岛的绝大部分。联合国安理会在苏联缺席的情况下通过决议，组成以美国为首的联合国军（由麦克阿瑟指挥）进行干预。9月的仁川登陆扭转战局，联合国军北上逼近鸭绿江。10月，中国人民志愿军跨过鸭绿江参战，将联合国军推回三八线以南。此后战争进入拉锯阶段，上甘岭战役等惨烈阵地战和谈判并行。1953年7月27日，《朝鲜停战协定》在板门店签署，但至今技术上仍处于战争状态。朝鲜战争是冷战从政治对抗转向军事冲突的标志，加深了中美对立，加速了日本的经济复兴，在朝鲜半岛留下了至今未解的冷战遗产。',
    descriptionEn: 'On June 25, 1950, North Korean forces crossed the 38th parallel southward, rapidly overrunning most of the peninsula. The UN Security Council, in the absence of the Soviet Union, authorized a US-led coalition (commanded by General MacArthur) to intervene. The September Inchon landing reversed the war\'s momentum, and UN forces pushed north toward the Yalu River. In October, Chinese People\'s Volunteers crossed the Yalu River, pushing UN forces back below the 38th parallel. The war thereafter devolved into a grinding stalemate with bloody battles like Heartbreak Ridge coexisting with truce negotiations. On July 27, 1953, the Korean Armistice Agreement was signed at Panmunjom, but the war technically continues to this day. The Korean War marked the Cold War\'s shift from political confrontation to military conflict, deepened Sino-American antagonism, accelerated Japan\'s economic recovery, and left a frozen Cold War legacy on the Korean Peninsula.',
