    summary: '埃及将苏伊士运河收归国有引发英法以三国入侵，在美国和苏联的共同压力下被迫撤军，标志着英法老牌殖民帝国的终结。',
    summaryEn: 'Egypt\'s nationalization of the Suez Canal prompted an Anglo-French-Israeli invasion, forced to withdraw under combined US-Soviet pressure, signaling the end of British and French imperial power.',
    description: '1956年7月26日，埃及总统纳赛尔在亚历山大港宣布将英法控制的苏伊士运河公司收归国有，以筹措阿斯旺大坝的建设资金。10月29日，以色列在英国和法国的秘密协议下入侵埃及西奈半岛；10月31日，英法以"保护运河"为名轰炸埃及并派兵登陆。这次行动没有事先知会美国，引发艾森豪威尔政府的震怒。在联合国大会上，美国和苏联罕见地一致要求英法以立即停火撤军。面对美苏两大超级大国的联合压力（包括美国威胁抛售英镑和苏联威胁使用火箭），英法于11月6日被迫接受停火并在12月完成撤军。苏伊士危机被视为英法作为全球帝国强权的"最后一役"，标志着后殖民时代美苏两极格局的正式确立。',
    descriptionEn: 'On July 26, 1956, Egyptian President Nasser announced in Alexandria the nationalization of the Anglo-French-controlled Suez Canal Company to fund the Aswan Dam. On October 29, Israel, under a secret agreement with Britain and France, invaded the Sinai Peninsula; on October 31, Britain and France bombed Egypt and landed troops under the pretext of "protecting the canal." The operation had not been coordinated with Washington, infuriating the Eisenhower administration. At the United Nations, the US and Soviet Union, in rare Cold War alignment, jointly demanded an immediate ceasefire and withdrawal. Facing unprecedented joint superpower pressure (including US threats to sell sterling and Soviet threats of rocket attacks), Britain and France accepted a ceasefire on November 6 and completed their withdrawal by December. The Suez Crisis is viewed as the "last hurrah" of British and French global imperial power and formally established the post-colonial US-Soviet bipolar order.',
