    importance: 5,
    summary: '越南人民军和越共在春节对南越全境发动大规模突然进攻，虽在军事上失败，但在政治上动摇了美国国内对战争的支持，成为越战转折点。',
    summaryEn: 'The North Vietnamese Army and Viet Cong launched a massive surprise offensive across South Vietnam during Tet. Though a military failure, it politically shattered American public support for the war, becoming the turning point of the Vietnam War.',
    description: '1968年1月30日（农历除夕），越南人民军和越南南方民族解放阵线（越共）出动约8万兵力，同时对南越100多个城镇和军事基地发动大规模进攻，包括攻入西贡的美国大使馆。攻势打破了此前双方约定的春节停火协定，因此称为"春节攻势"。尽管美军和南越军在数周内将越共逐出各城市并造成对方惨重伤亡（越共估计损失4-5万人），但春节攻势在心理和政治上产生了颠覆性效果。美国国内此前一直被告知"战争即将胜利"，春节攻势通过电视直播的画面粉碎了这一叙事。著名新闻主播沃尔特·克朗凯特在电视上宣称战争已陷入僵局。林登·约翰逊总统随后宣布不寻求连任，美国开始逐步从越南撤军。',
    descriptionEn: 'On January 30, 1968 (Lunar New Year\'s Eve), approximately 80,000 North Vietnamese Army and Viet Cong troops launched coordinated attacks on more than 100 towns and military installations across South Vietnam, including storming the US Embassy in Saigon. The offensive violated a previously agreed Tet ceasefire—hence the name "Tet Offensive." Although US and South Vietnamese forces ejected the attackers from urban centers within weeks and inflicted devastating casualties (an estimated 40,000-50,000 Viet Cong losses), the Tet Offensive produced a seismic psychological and political impact. The American public had been told repeatedly that "victory was near"; televised footage of the offensive shattered that narrative. Legendary news anchor Walter Cronkite declared on air the war was a stalemate. President Lyndon Johnson soon announced he would not seek reelection, and America began the gradual withdrawal from Vietnam.',
