    summary: '霍梅尼领导的伊斯兰革命推翻巴列维王朝，建立了以什叶派教法学家监护体制为基础的伊斯兰共和国，深刻重塑了中东地缘政治。',
    summaryEn: 'The Islamic Revolution led by Ayatollah Khomeini overthrew the Pahlavi dynasty and established an Islamic Republic based on Shia clerical guardianship, fundamentally reshaping Middle Eastern geopolitics.',
    description: '1979年1月16日，统治伊朗长达37年的国王穆罕默德·礼萨·巴列维被迫流亡海外，结束了拥有2500年历史的波斯君主制。这场革命由流亡法国的什叶派宗教领袖大阿亚图拉鲁霍拉·霍梅尼领导，汇集了左翼学生、中产阶级、商人和宗教人士等广泛的反对派联盟。2月1日，霍梅尼从巴黎返回德黑兰受到数百万人迎接。4月1日全民公投以98%的赞成票通过建立伊斯兰共和国，随后通过的新宪法确立了"教法学家监护"（Velayat-e Faqih）制度——赋予最高领袖凌驾于民选机构的最终权力。11月，学生冲击美国大使馆将52名美国人扣为人质444天，导致美伊断交至今。伊朗革命是20世纪最具影响力的社会政治变革之一，催生了中东政治伊斯兰运动的兴起。',
    descriptionEn: 'On January 16, 1979, Shah Mohammad Reza Pahlavi, who had ruled Iran for 37 years, was forced into exile, ending 2,500 years of Persian monarchy. The revolution was led from exile in France by Grand Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini and united a broad coalition of leftist students, the middle class, bazaar merchants, and clergy. On February 1, Khomeini returned to Tehran to a welcome by millions. A referendum on April 1 approved the establishment of an Islamic Republic with 98% of the vote. The new constitution established the principle of "Velayat-e Faqih" (Guardianship of the Jurist), giving the Supreme Leader ultimate authority over elected institutions. In November, students stormed the US Embassy, holding 52 Americans hostage for 444 days and rupturing US-Iranian relations to this day. The Iranian Revolution ranks among the most consequential socio-political transformations of the 20th century, catalyzing the rise of political Islamism across the Middle East.',
